name: Monkpath
description: If the poster "enlightenment " is simple in its form, and similar to the idea of emptiness. Then this poster is speculating on the Tibetan book of the dead. Death is all that ends and no more. All things are nothing. And therefore nothing. All things are one, and therefore one, and therefore one. No individual image is really like this. They are just moving sides of a black mass. The main issue between any two of these is then exactly the same argument (other which has not been mentioned). Just
